Understood what's going on. In 20021016 build, PDECore startup is resetting
the worskace model manager

public void startup() throws CoreException {
  super.startup();
  loadSettings();
  workspaceModelManager = new WorkspaceModelManager();
>>workspaceModelManager.reset();
  modelManager = new PluginModelManager();
}

which may now do extra work on modelManager (which hasn't been set yet, see 
startup code).

public ExternalModelManager getExternalModelManager() {
  if (externalModelManager == null) {
    externalModelManager = new ExternalModelManager();
>>>>modelManager.connect(workspaceModelManager,externalModelManager);
  }
  return externalModelManager;
}

Suggested fix is to swap lines in startup code to read:

public void startup() throws CoreException {
  super.startup();
  loadSettings();
  workspaceModelManager = new WorkspaceModelManager();
  modelManager = new PluginModelManager();
  workspaceModelManager.reset();
}

Tried this patch, and everything was back to normal.
